[size=2][i]Nexus description in BBCode. Set the mission patch (branding/osf-patch.png) as the mod's
main/thumbnail image in the Nexus UI. Upload branding/osf-header.png, the five section headers
(packaging/section-headers/0*.png), and your in-game screenshots to the mod's image gallery, then paste
each one's Nexus-hosted URL into the [img] tags below (the file paths here are placeholders — Nexus only
renders images it hosts). Screenshot shot-list: scene browser open in the world, the emote wheel radial,
a synced multi-actor scene, a creature clip playing, the orbit camera framing a scene.
Replace REPLACE-WITH-OSFUI-NEXUS-URL with OSF UI's mod page URL once it is live.[/i][/size]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/osf-header.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=5][b]Browse, play, and sync every animation in Starfield.[/b][/size][/center]

[center][i]An in-game scene browser over 4,600+ base-game animations — humans, creatures, robots — plus an emote wheel, synced multi-actor scenes, and the open scene engine underneath.[/i][/center]

[line]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/01-overview.png[/img][/center]

OSF — [b]Open Scene Framework[/b] — is an animation and scene engine with a player-facing front end. Out of the box:

[list]
[*][b]Scene browser[/b] — an in-game overlay (press [b]F10[/b]). Pick a scene, cast yourself or nearby NPCs, play. Keyboard and gamepad navigable.
[*][b]Animation library[/b] — 4,600+ animations from the base game, browsable and filterable: idles, furniture, combat, chargen poses, photo-mode idles, and 27 creature/robot species from Terrormorphs to security cameras. Furniture clips anchor to real furniture in the world.
[*][b]Highlights[/b] — curated collections (300 hand-picked clips) so the first open is worth watching, not a wall of filenames.
[*][b]Emote wheel[/b] — a radial menu of emotes (wave, what's up, hands on hips, arms crossed, data slate). Play them on yourself — or on the NPC in your crosshair.
[*][b]Scene camera[/b] — an orbit camera that frames the cast automatically; mouse to orbit and zoom.
[/list]

Underneath sits the engine: synced multi-actor playback on one shared clock, world/furniture anchoring, JSON-authored scene graphs, and a Papyrus API. OSF is built to power other mods — machinima, dance packs, NPC vignettes, quest scenes.

[line]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/02-features.png[/img][/center]

[list]
[*]Synced multi-actor [b]AF / GLTF / GLB[/b] playback on one shared frame clock
[*]Data-driven [b]scene graphs[/b] — nodes, cues, actions, callbacks, branching — authored in JSON, no scripting required
[*][b]World and furniture anchoring[/b] — scenes pin to chairs, beds, consoles, or any reference
[*]Engine-native [b]Wwise[/b] audio (rides the game's mix) with real subtitle support
[*]Player-control and camera locks, full-screen fades, equipment hide/restore — all reversed by an [b]undo ledger[/b] on any exit, including crashes-of-plan like combat or loading a save. Mid-scene saves are scrubbed safe.
[*]Settings and rebindable hotkeys live in [b]OSF UI's in-game settings menu[/b] (browser and emote-wheel keys, log level, first-run hint)
[*]A [b]Papyrus API[/b] ([font=Courier New]OSF.*[/font]) for quest and consumer mods
[/list]

[line]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/03-get-started.png[/img][/center]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/starfield/mods/106]SFSE[/url] matching your game version
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/starfield/mods/3256]Address Library for SFSE Plugins[/url]
[*][url=REPLACE-WITH-OSFUI-NEXUS-URL]OSF UI[/url] — hosts the scene browser, emote wheel, settings, and hotkeys. The engine runs without it, but you lose the entire in-game UI; install it.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]
Install with a mod manager (Mod Organizer 2 / Vortex). The FOMOD installer offers two content options — keep both:
[list]
[*][b]Animation Library[/b] — the browsable vanilla + creature catalog (pure JSON, a few MB, no plugin slot)
[*][b]Emote Wheel Content[/b] — the emote pack the wheel shows
[/list]

[size=4][b]Try it (30 seconds)[/b][/size]
Load a save, press [b]F10[/b], open the [b]Highlights[/b] collections, pick anything, hit play. Add a nearby NPC to the cast and play a paired scene. To verify the engine from the console (~):
[code]cgf "OSF.Health"[/code]

[size=4][b]Hotkeys[/b][/size]
The emote wheel ships unbound — set its key (and rebind the browser) in OSF UI's settings menu, on the OSF Animation card. Keys never fire while the console or a text field has focus.

[line]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/04-for-authors.png[/img][/center]

[list]
[*][b]Pack authors:[/b] ship scenes as JSON + GLB/AF clips. No Papyrus, no scripting. Tag a solo scene [font=Courier New]player.emote.*[/font] and it appears in the emote wheel automatically.
[*][b]Quest / consumer mods:[/b] drive scenes from Papyrus via the [font=Courier New]OSF.*[/font] API — start scenes by tag query, advance and navigate graphs, receive callbacks, use the anchor system.
[/list]
Full documentation — Getting Started, Scene Schema, and the Papyrus API — is on [url=https://github.com/ozooma10/osf-animation]GitHub[/url].

[size=4][b]Compatibility & content policy[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]SFW.[/b] The engine and all bundled content are content-neutral; no adult assets. Specific content lives in separate mods built on top.
[*]Adapted from [b]NativeAnimationFrameworkSF (NAF)[/b]; it is its own framework, not a drop-in NAF/SAF replacement.
[*]Built for the current Starfield + SFSE; on an unsupported game version it logs a clear warning and self-disables features rather than crashing.
[/list]

[line]

[center][img]REPLACE-WITH-NEXUS-URL/05-credits.png[/img][/center]

OSF Animation is [b]open source[/b] (GPL-3.0 with a modding/linking exception). Full source, build instructions, and issue tracker: [url=https://github.com/ozooma10/osf-animation]github.com/ozooma10/osf-animation[/url]. Bug reports and pull requests welcome.

[list]
[*][b]Deweh[/b] — [url=https://github.com/Deweh/NativeAnimationFrameworkSF]NativeAnimationFrameworkSF[/url] (GPL-3.0), the ozz playback/graph foundation OSF is adapted from
[*][b]Calaverah[/b] — [url=https://github.com/Calaverah/CALUMI.Animation]CALUMI.Animation[/url] (LGPL-3.0), the engine-native .af / skeleton.rig decoder
[*][b]CommonLibSF[/b], fastgltf, ozz-animation, zlib, nlohmann/json, and miniaudio
[/list]
Full attributions and licenses are in THIRD_PARTY.md in the repository.
